Women are always shamed for being too free, too conservative, too curvy, too skinny, too professional, too wild, too much, too little. 

I’m judged for expressing myself outside the box of motherhood. But you know what, my identity is up to me. I lived a traditional life before: dating long term, to marriage, to buying a house, to having a baby. I do not regret any of it but let this be a lesson that there is no ONE right way to live your life. There is no guarantee that things will work out or won’t work out for you. Everyday is a new day, neither you or anyone else can predict it. 

Be patient with yourself babes and live whatever freakin’ life you want 🌹

Remember to take care of yourself first. 👏🏻 In any circumstance because when you are happy, collected, and satisfied.. it will reflect on everyone around you. ☀️ Especially mothers, as a lot of women choose to sacrifice so many things for their children (rightfully so). WHO DOESN’T LOVE SLIME?! 🤩

You can engage in this super fun activity at the @kidsslimeclub located in the @plazawestcovina mall in the Los Angeles area. 
📍 705 Plaza Dr, West Covina, CA 91790

Here your child can enjoy creating their own slime and customizing it to their little heart’s content. ❤️

There are different types of slime available with their own unique attributes. 
Pricing is reasonable and every mix-in is just $1. 

We started with level one ($10.95 w/ one mix-in included) and plan to move up every visit! ☺️

They have themed (including the Grinch, Pokemon, Super Mario, Barbie, Nightmare Before Christmas, etc.) events and DIY kits available. ✨

I have always been a parent that values experiences over material things when it comes to “spoiling” my child. This slime shop is a great concept and I hope that they continue to provide this frugal, fun activity to kids in the community. With that being said, I saw that @kidsslimeclub is struggling financially which is such a common occurrence of non-chain businesses nowadays and they have set up a GoFund me for those interested in helping. Check out their profile for more info. 🫶🏻

STOP LETTING WHAT YOU SEE ON SOCIAL MEDIA, ECT MAKE YOU FEEL LIKE YOU ARE NOT VALUABLE AS IS. I promise you, so much of what you see on here is 🐂 💩. I have blocked so many accounts I’ve lost track because I’m just so tired of seeing the same airbrushed, BBL, tummy tuck belly button, filler, filtered, posed look. If that’s what you like then cool, but that’s not what I’m about. How am I supposed to teach my child to value himself or others if all I do is change my authentic self? So many children are going to grow up and look nothing like their mothers and that’s sad to me. I can’t even imagine having a daughter in this world because it would break my heart to see her feel like she isn’t perfect because of how the media portrays this fantasy. The justification of “well this is what makes me happy” is not real to me. That’s like bringing food to a potluck and everyone raves about it but lo and behold, you bought it at your local grocery store premade and stuffed it in a home pan. We need to do better as a society, both men and women.
